artist.org/media/CO2_Temp_FRF_1st_detrend.png\n\nHaving spent quite a bit of time on this, I\u2019m convinced that changes in\ntemperature over the last fifty years cannot be attributed to CO2, unless it\ncan be shown that time runs backwards.\n\n       * bdgwx says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 11:18 AM\n\nCO2 did not follow temperature during the PETM nor is it following temperature\ntoday. Instead it got released independently via volcanic activity and human\nactivity respectively.\n\n       * Willard says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 12:29 PM\n\nPerhaps, but pirates obviously cause global cooling.\n\nArrr!\n\n       * Stephen P. Anderson says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 12:30 PM\n\nBGDWX,\n\nWe know temperature doesn\u2019t and never has followed CO2 because we\u2019re still\nhere.\n\n       * bdgwx says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 12:50 PM\n\nSPA, let me make sure I\u2019m understanding your point. Are you saying that humans\ncould not have released CO2 into the atmosphere independent of temperature\nbecause if we did then we wouldn\u2019t exist? Yes/No?\n\n       * Arkady Ivanovich says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 1:47 PM\n\nRobert Cutler\n\nI can appreciate the effort you\u2019ve put into this work, and I congratulate you\non it, but for me statistics cannot answer the question, what happens to\ninfrared radiation emitted by the Earth\u2019s surface? You need a mechanistic\nmodel.\n\n       * Nate says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 3:54 PM\n\n\u201cIn short, for periods from 2-10 years, and likely longer, CO2 lags\ntemperature by six months\u201d\n\nRobert, makes sense, because those are the time scales of ENSO or the seasons,\nand we know that CO2 responds to those T changes.\n\nBut for the decadal and longer growth of CO2, there is no evidence T caused\nthe unprecedented CO2 growth this last century.\n\n       * Stephen P. Anderson says:\n\nMay 3, 2024 at 6:46 PM\n\nBDGWX,\n\nWhy haven\u2019t high excursion in CO2 in the past caused higher temperatures that\ncaused even higher CO2 and so on? We wouldn\u2019t be her