first law of motion.\n\n\u201cProjectiles persevere in their motions, so far as they are not retarded by\nthe resistance of the air, or impelled downwards by the force of gravity. A\ntop, whose parts by their cohesion are perpetually drawn aside from\nrectilinear motions, does not cease its rotation, otherwise than as it is\nretarded by the air. The greater bodies of the planets and comets, meeting\nwith less resistance in more free spaces, preserve their motions both\nprogressive and circular for a much longer time.\u201d\n\nHe understood that the pull of gravity in no way changes the axial rotation\n(or lack of it) of an object.\n\n       * Dr Roys Emergency Moderation Team says:\n\nMay 6, 2024 at 1:39 AM\n\nStill nothing.\n\n       * Willard says:\n\nMay 6, 2024 at 8:03 AM\n\nGraham D. Warner always ends up gaslighting.\n\n       * Dr Roys Emergency Moderation Team says:\n\nMay 6, 2024 at 9:29 AM\n\nAgain: still nothing.\n\n  42. gbaikie says:\n\nMay 4, 2024 at 4:27 PM\n\nSpaceX\u2019s Massive Updates for Flight 4 are Astounding!\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f7Hr-4O4N5g\n\nAnd talks about the Saxavord Spaceport and also China lunar mission to return\nsamples from South PoleAitken basin.\n\nReply\n\n  43. Gordon Robertson says:\n\nMay 4, 2024 at 5:51 PM\n\nbinny...\u201dVournas #2\n\nI repeat: go to\n\nhttps://www.noa.gr\n\ntell them your simple-minded nonsense, and come back with their answer (I hope\nyou will be honest enough not to misrepresent it)\u201d.\n\n***\n\nChristos is polite to everyone on this site even you. Why is it, in your\nblatant ignorance, you cannot address him politely?\n\nReply\n\n  44. Gordon Robertson says:\n\nMay 4, 2024 at 6:09 PM\n\nark...\u201dSir Isaac Newton worked 7 days a week, 18 hours a day. He had given up\nhis personal life, he probably never had any intention of getting married or\nraising a family. He wanted to devote all his life to the works of science and\nthe pursuit of mathematics and so he did\u201d.\n\n***\n\nYour 